    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="756"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">700.022/11–1550</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Legal Adviser for European Affairs</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Yingling</hi>) <hi rend="italic">to Mr. Edwin D.
                        Dickinson</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-01">November 1,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Dickinson</hi>: Reference is made to our
                    telephone conversation of a few days ago at which time you indicated that you
                    would be available for an informal interdepartmental conference on territorial
                    waters.</p>
                <pb facs="1709" n="1693" xml:id="pg_1693"/>
                <p>We have arranged for representatives of other interested departments of the
                    government to come to Mr. Fisher’s office, Room 4264 New State Department
                    Building, at 2:00 p. m. on November 8, 1950. We will look forward to seeing you
                    at that time. I have arranged for travel requisitions to be sent to you.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Raymund</hi> T. <hi rend="smallcaps">Yingling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
